---
import Exercise from "@/components/Articles/Exercise/Exercise.astro";
import Keyword from "@/components/Articles/Keyword.astro";
---

<Exercise class="mb-20" exercise={2} title="Implementing Number Handling">
  <p>
    You now have everything you need to implement <strong
      >number scanning</strong
    >. The logic follows the exact same pattern as <strong
      >letter scanning</strong
    > — use the animation above to build your intuition.
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>
      Implement <Keyword word="isNumber()" /> — similar to <Keyword
        word="isLetter()"
      />.
    </li>
    <li>
      Implement <Keyword word="readNumber()" /> — similar to <Keyword
        word="readIdent()"
      />.
    </li>
    <li>Add the corresponding case inside <Keyword word="NextToken()" />.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    💡 <strong>Need help?</strong> Check the full implementation in the <a
      href="https://github.com/dyxgou/redis/blob/ebbb821dc3e9b8743190cd728fd11678aae9e731/pkg/lexer/lexer.go#L102"
      rel="noopener noreferer"
      target="_blank">pkg/lexer/lexer.go</a
    > file of the source code. And if you still have questions, don't hesitate to
    reach out on <a
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferer"
      href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/diego-alejandro-417357219/">LinkedIn</a
    >.
  </p>
</Exercise>
